						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarājakēsarivarman: Year 10 = 994-95 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription refers to the king as ‘who destroyed the ships at Śālai’.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of 20 <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> of paddy to provide for offerings at the service held at noon on the days when the asterism Āyilyam fell every month to the god Mahādēvar of Tiruneḍuṅgaḷam in [Kavira]-nāḍu by a certain <hi rend="italic">Veḷḷāḷaṉ</hi> (name lost) of the place. It is stated that the endorsement was accepted by the temple priests who had agreed to carry out the object of the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
